So far the best way to limit the input is using a poller advice.

This pauses the poller once the thread queue is bigger than two times the core threads:

```
public class ThreadQueueAwareReceiveMessageAdvice implements ReceiveMessageAdvice {
    private final ThreadPoolTaskExecutor taskExecutor;
    private int maxThreadQueue;

    public ThreadQueueAwareReceiveMessageAdvice(ThreadPoolTaskExecutor taskExecutor) {
        this.taskExecutor = taskExecutor;
        this.maxThreadQueue = 2 * taskExecutor.getCorePoolSize();
    }

    @Override
    public boolean beforeReceive(Object source) {
        if (taskExecutor.getQueueSize() &gt;= maxThreadQueue) {
            return false;
        }
        return ReceiveMessageAdvice.super.beforeReceive(source);
    }

    @Override
    public Message&lt;?&gt; afterReceive(Message&lt;?&gt; result, Object source) {
        return result;
    }
}
